---
import LegalPage from "../components/LegalPage.astro";
import { landingContent } from "../content";
---

<LegalPage
  title="Terms of Service"
  description="The terms that apply when you download, access, or use Chronicle and its optional online services."
  eyebrow="Clear terms. Creative freedom."
  effectiveDate="July 22, 2026"
  currentPath="/terms-and-services/"
>
  <Fragment slot="navigation">
    <a href="#agreement">Agreement</a>
    <a href="#service">The service</a>
    <a href="#accounts">Accounts</a>
    <a href="#your-content">Your content</a>
    <a href="#ai">AI features</a>
    <a href="#acceptable-use">Acceptable use</a>
    <a href="#disclaimers">Disclaimers</a>
    <a href="#contact">Contact</a>
  </Fragment>

  <section id="agreement">
    <span class="legal-section-number">01</span>
    <h2>Your agreement with Chronicle</h2>
    <p>
      These Terms of Service (the "Terms") govern your download, access, and use of Chronicle, including the
      desktop application, website, and optional online services (together, the "Service"). By using the
      Service, you agree to these Terms and our{" "}<a href="/privacy/">Privacy Policy</a>. If you do not agree, do
      not use the Service.
    </p>
    <p>
      You must be legally able to enter into this agreement and meet the minimum digital-consent age that
      applies where you live. If you use Chronicle for an organization, you confirm that you can accept these
      Terms for that organization.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="service">
    <span class="legal-section-number">02</span>
    <h2>What Chronicle provides</h2>
    <p>
      Chronicle is a local-first tool that watches folders you select, captures changed versions of supported
      creative files, stores a local history, and helps you search and restore that history. Optional AI
      features can describe changes and create semantic-search embeddings. Core local features do not require
      an account or Chronicle's online service. Google Sign-In enables account-backed features such as portable
      settings. Encrypted provider-key sync is separate and requires you to enable it and save an encrypted copy.
      Chronicle does not provide cloud storage for your creative version library.
    </p>
    <p>
      The current release can register a random installation identifier when its configured service is
      reachable, including in local mode. Its usage-reporting preference starts enabled, but transmission of
      usage events and the related admin analytics view are not implemented in the current release. The
      Privacy Policy explains these boundaries and will be updated before those capabilities materially change.
    </p>
    <p>
      Chronicle is under active development. Supported formats, compatibility, limits, and features may change.
      We may modify, suspend, or discontinue all or part of the Service, and we will provide reasonable notice
      when a material change adversely affects users where practical.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="accounts">
    <span class="legal-section-number">03</span>
    <h2>Accounts and Google Sign-In</h2>
    <p>
      An account is optional. If you create one with Google Sign-In, you authorize Chronicle to use the basic
      identity information described on the consent screen and in our Privacy Policy to authenticate you. You
      are responsible for maintaining control of your Google account, your device, and any Chronicle session.
      Notify us promptly if you believe your account or session has been compromised.
    </p>
    <p>
      You may not impersonate another person, misrepresent your affiliation, transfer access in a way that
      undermines security, or attempt to bypass authentication or account controls. We may suspend or deactivate
      access when reasonably necessary to protect the Service, comply with law, or address a material breach of
      these Terms.
    </p>
    <p>
      Portable settings sync can be disabled in Settings. The current control starts enabled but cannot sync
      anything until you choose to sign in. Provider keys stay encrypted on your device by default. If you
      separately enable key sync, Chronicle stores only the passphrase-encrypted envelope created on your
      device, not your passphrase, plaintext provider keys, or decryption key.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="your-content">
    <span class="legal-section-number">04</span>
    <h2>Your files remain your files</h2>
    <p>
      You retain all rights in the files and other content you process with Chronicle. These Terms do not give
      Chronicle ownership of your creative work. You give Chronicle only the limited permission needed to read,
      copy, index, restore, and otherwise process content on your device at your direction, and to send specific
      inputs to an AI provider when you enable and use an AI feature.
    </p>
    <p>
      You are responsible for having the rights and permissions needed to process your content. Chronicle is a
      version-history aid, not your only backup. You should maintain independent backups of important work and
      check restored files before relying on them.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="ai">
    <span class="legal-section-number">05</span>
    <h2>AI features and provider services</h2>
    <p>
      AI summaries, tags, and search results are generated automatically and may be inaccurate, incomplete, or
      misleading. Review AI output before relying on it, especially for professional, legal, safety-critical, or
      irreversible decisions. Chronicle does not guarantee that AI output will identify every visual change.
    </p>
    <p>
      When you connect your own AI provider, you are also subject to that provider's terms, privacy policy,
      pricing, quotas, and content rules. You are responsible for provider charges and for ensuring your use is
      permitted. Chronicle is not responsible for a third-party provider's availability, output, retention, or
      handling of data sent at your direction.
    </p>
    <p>
      AI work may queue while you are offline and be processed when the selected provider becomes reachable.
      You can continue capturing and browsing local versions without enabling AI.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="software">
    <span class="legal-section-number">06</span>
    <h2>Software and open-source components</h2>
    <p>
      Chronicle's source code is made available through its{" "}
      <a href={landingContent.githubUrl}>public repository</a>. Your right to copy, modify, or distribute source
      code is governed by the license files included with that code. Third-party and open-source components may
      have separate terms. These Terms govern your use of the hosted website, account services, and any aspects
      not covered by an applicable software license.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="acceptable-use">
    <span class="legal-section-number">07</span>
    <h2>Acceptable use</h2>
    <p>You agree not to use the Service to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>break the law or infringe another person's privacy, intellectual-property, or other rights;</li>
      <li>upload, process, or transmit content you do not have the right to use;</li>
      <li>introduce malware, abuse infrastructure, interfere with other users, or evade rate or security limits;</li>
      <li>probe, attack, reverse engineer, or access non-public systems except where law or an open-source license permits it;</li>
      <li>use automated means that materially burden the Service; or</li>
      <li>use AI features to create or facilitate unlawful or harmful activity.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section id="disclaimers">
    <span class="legal-section-number">08</span>
    <h2>Disclaimers</h2>
    <p>
      To the fullest extent permitted by law, the Service is provided "as is" and "as available." We disclaim
      implied warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, non-infringement, and uninterrupted
      or error-free operation. We do not warrant that Chronicle will capture every save, preserve every file,
      work with every editor, or produce accurate AI output. Nothing in these Terms excludes warranties that
      cannot legally be excluded.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="liability">
    <span class="legal-section-number">09</span>
    <h2>Limitation of liability</h2>
    <p>
      To the fullest extent permitted by law, the Chronicle project team and contributors will not be liable for
      indirect, incidental, special, consequential, exemplary, or punitive damages, or for loss of content, data,
      profits, goodwill, or business opportunity arising from the Service. Our total liability for claims relating
      to the Service will not exceed the greater of the amount you paid us for the Service during the 12 months
      before the claim or USD $100. These limits do not apply where prohibited by law.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="termination">
    <span class="legal-section-number">10</span>
    <h2>Ending use of Chronicle</h2>
    <p>
      You may stop using Chronicle at any time. Uninstalling the app or signing out does not necessarily remove
      local app data, synced settings, or your Chronicle account. You can delete an encrypted key-sync copy from
      Settings. A self-service account-deletion button is not implemented in the current release, so contact us
      to request deletion of the account and its associated server-side data. Account deletion does not delete
      local version history unless you separately remove it on your device. We may suspend or end online access
      for a serious or repeated breach, security risk, legal requirement, or discontinuation of the Service.
      Provisions that by their nature should survive termination, including ownership, disclaimers, and liability
      limits, will survive.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="general">
    <span class="legal-section-number">11</span>
    <h2>Changes and general terms</h2>
    <p>
      We may update these Terms as Chronicle changes. We will post the revised Terms, update the effective date,
      and provide additional notice for material changes where required. If a provision is unenforceable, the
      remaining provisions stay in effect. Our failure to enforce a provision is not a waiver. You may not assign
      these Terms without our consent; we may assign them as part of a reorganization or transfer of the project.
    </p>
    <p>
      Mandatory consumer protections and the courts available to you under applicable law are not limited by
      these Terms. Any dispute should first be raised with us so the parties can try to resolve it informally.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="contact">
    <span class="legal-section-number">12</span>
    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Chronicle is maintained by the Chronicle project team. Questions about these Terms can be sent to{" "}
      <a href="mailto:chronicle.support@gmial.com">chronicle.support@gmial.com</a>{" "}or submitted through the{" "}
      <a href={`${landingContent.githubUrl}/issues`} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Chronicle project issue tracker</a>.
      Do not publish passwords, provider keys, tokens, file contents, or other sensitive information in an issue.
    </p>
  </section>
</LegalPage>
